# Discord Chat Analysis: "core-devs" Channel

## 1. Summary
The discussion primarily focused on technical aspects of building a Farcaster character called "frok" and implementing browser-based capabilities for ElizaOS. Shaw proposed creating a Farcaster character as a marketing initiative, with a 3-week timeline. CJFT advocated for browser-based implementation of ElizaOS, highlighting the benefits of running AgentRuntime and DB directly in the browser rather than using websockets. They discussed text-to-speech options, comparing ElevenLabs (high quality but requiring API proxying) versus browser-based models like VITS-web and HeadTTS (faster but potentially lower quality). Authentication was identified as a critical issue, with discussions about JWT implementation versus the current X-API-KEY approach. The chat also revealed a security concern with hardcoded Supabase credentials in the codebase. Stan and sayonara agreed to collaborate on the Farcaster character project. CJFT mentioned upcoming PRs for PGLite WASM and browser compatibility improvements, positioning these as key components for ElizaOS 2.0.
